metadata.name: Workers Leaving The Lumière Factory
metadata.description:
Workers Leaving The Lumière Factory in Lyon (French: La Sortie de l'Usine Lumière à Lyon), also known as Employees Leaving the Lumière Factory and Exiting the Factory, is an 1895 French short black-and-white silent documentary film directed and produced by Louis Lumière. It is often referred to as the first real motion picture ever made.
This film is the first film in the history of world cinema. I submitted it as nft. This film is very valuable because it was the first.
